Preheat your #oven{} to 180°C. Boil your #kettle{}. Bring a #saucepan{} of water to the boil with a pinch of @salt{pinch} for the potatoes.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on medium heat. Peel the @garlic clove{2}(peeled). Halve the @echalion shallot{1}(peeled) lengthways and peel. Lay the shallot cut side down in the pan with the garlic. Brown for ~{4-5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #jug{}, dissolve half the @red wine stock paste{28%g} with the @water for the stock{100%ml} for the shallot.

Transfer the browned shallot and garlic to a small #ovenproof dish{} (don't wash the pan). Add half the @thyme{1/2}(sprigs), pour in the stock and cover with #foil{}. Bake on the middle shelf until soft, ~{25-30%minutes}. Uncover for the final ~{5%minutes} and remove and reserve the garlic.

Meanwhile, peel and chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks. Boil the potatoes until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{12-15%minutes}. Drain in a #colander{}. Return to the pan, off the heat, with the #lid{} on.

Meanwhile, trim the @chantenay carrots{250%g}(trimmed) (no need to peel). Pop on a #baking tray{} and drizzle with @oil{drizzle}. Season with @salt{pinch} and @ground black pepper{pinch} and roast on the top shelf of the oven until soft and golden, ~{20-25%minutes}, turning halfway.

Meanwhile, return the frying pan to medium heat. When hot, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{60%g} and fry until golden, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Meanwhile, roughly tear the @shiitake mushrooms{50%g}(roughly torn). Transfer the pancetta to a #bowl{} and wipe the pan. We will use it again later.

Put the @21 day aged British fillet steaks{2} on a #plate{} and season on both sides with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.  When the potatoes are ready, add the cooked garlic and @unsalted butter{30%g} to the pan. Use a #stick blender{} to puree the potatoes until smooth. Season to taste and cover.

> TIP: If you don't have a stick blender, mash the garlic with a fork, use a potato masher for the potatoes and mix well.

Heat a splash of @oil{splash} in the frying pan over high heat. When hot, lay in the steaks. Brown all over, ~{2%minutes}, lower the heat slightly and cook for ~{3-4%minutes} per side.

> TIP: This will give you medium-rare; if you like your steak a little more done, cook for an extra 2 mins per side.

When the steaks have 4 mins left, add the shiitakes and remaining thyme. Cook for ~{3-4%minutes}. Transfer everything to a plate and wrap loosely in foil.

Add the @water for the sauce{100%ml} and remaining stock pot to the pan. Bring to the boil then lower the heat, stir in the pancetta and simmer until glossy, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Meanwhile, reheat the puree if needed.

Slice the steak into 5 pieces. Spoon 3 dollops of puree on each plate. Use the back of a #spoon{} to drag it out in lines. Top with the steak and shallot. Arrange the roasted carrots and shiitakes around and drizzle with sauce.